wikibaselexeme-error-cannot-remove-last-: Error message that is being reported when the last lemma is being removed.
wikibaselexeme-api-error-parameter-requi: API error message that is being reported when parameter is missing.
wikibaselexeme-api-error-parameter-inval: API error message that is being reported when provided data parameter is not a valid JSON
wikibaselexeme-api-error-lexeme-not-foun:
API error message that is being reported when Lexeme with provided ID does not exist.

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the field
* $2 - ID of the Lexeme
wikibaselexeme-api-error-form-not-found:
API error message that is being reported when lexicographical Form with provided ID does not exist.

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the field
* $2 - ID of the lexicographical Form
wikibaselexeme-api-error-sense-not-found:
API error message that is being reported when Sense with provided ID does not exist.

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the field
* $2 - ID of the Sense
wikibaselexeme-api-error-json-field-requ:
API error message that is being reported when required field in JSON object is not present. 

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the parameter that is expected to be JSON object. 
* $2 - Path of the field inside of the JSON object (e.g "array-field-name/0/other-field-name")
wikibaselexeme-api-error-json-field-not-:
API error message that is being reported when field in JSON object expected to contain serialized Item ID, but contains something else. 

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the parameter that is expected to be JSON object.
* $2 - Path of the field inside of the JSON object (e.g "array-field-name/0/other-field-name")
* $3 - Provided value
wikibaselexeme-api-error-json-field-has-:
API error message that is being reported when field in JSON object expected to be of certain type, but value of another type was provided. 

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the parameter that is expected to be JSON object.
* $2 - Path of the field inside of the JSON object (e.g "array-field-name/0/other-field-name")
* $3 - Expected type name (e.g. string, array, object) 
* $4 - Provided value type name
wikibaselexeme-api-error-parameter-not-l:
API error message that is being reported when parameter is expected to contain serialized Lexeme ID, but contains something else. 

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the parameter
* $2 - Provided value
wikibaselexeme-api-error-parameter-not-f:
API error message that is being reported when parameter is expected to contain serialized lexicographical Form ID, but contains something else. 

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the parameter
* $2 - Provided value
wikibaselexeme-api-error-parameter-not-s:
API error message that is being reported when parameter is expected to contain serialized Sense ID, but contains something else. 

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the parameter
* $2 - Provided value
wikibaselexeme-api-error-lexeme-term-tex: API error message that is being reported when one of provided representations or lemmas is empty
wikibaselexeme-api-error-lexeme-term-lan: API error message that is being reported when the language of one of provided representations or lemmas is empty
wikibaselexeme-api-error-language-incons:
API error message that is being reported when language of provided representation or lemma is inconsistent.

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the parameter that is expected to be JSON object.
* $2 - Path of the field inside of the JSON object (e.g "array-field-name/0/other-field-name")
* $3 - Expected language
* $4 - Given language
wikibaselexeme-api-error-form-must-have-: API error message that is being reported when no lexicographical Form representations were provided
wikibaselexeme-api-error-sense-must-have: API error message that is reported when no glosses were provided
wikibaselexeme-api-error-unknown-languag: API error message that is being reported when the language field contains an unknown language.
wikibaselexeme-api-error-invalid-item-id: API error message that is being reported when the language of a lexeme term contains an unknown item id.
